```
$ box --help
A Rust CLI toolbox

Usage: box[EXE] [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  flatten      Flatten a folder tree into a single output directory
  uuid         Generate a random UUID
  base64       Encode or decode base64 text
  epoch        Convert between Unix timestamps and human-readable dates
  color        Convert colors between hex and RGB formats
  passgen      Generate secure passwords and passphrases
  cowsay       Wrap text in an ASCII-art speech bubble
  fortune      Print a random fortune or quote
  8ball        Ask the magic 8-ball a question
  roast        Deliver a random programmer roast
  hash         Compute and verify file hashes
  tree         Print a directory tree with file sizes
  du           Analyze disk usage for a directory
  dupes        Find duplicate files by content
  bulk-rename  Bulk-rename files with a regex and dry-run preview
  lolcat       Rainbow-colorize piped text
  matrix       Run the Matrix digital-rain screensaver effect
  ascii        Render an image as ASCII art
  json         Pretty-print and validate JSON
  qr           Render a QR code for text or a URL in the terminal
  clip         Read from or write to the system clipboard
  pomodoro     Run a focus timer with Windows toast notifications
  weather      Fetch the weather for a location
  config       Read, edit, and locate the box config file
  help         Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --no-color  Disable colored output (also honors NO_COLOR and non-TTY stdout)
      --json      Emit machine-readable JSON on stdout (suppresses color/progress)
      --clip      Copy the command's output to the clipboard (also prints it)
  -h, --help      Print help
  -V, --version   Print version

```
